  "local_port": 50720,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you deposit cash at an ATM?",
  "response": "Depositing cash at an ATM typically involves the following steps, though the exact process can vary slightly depending on your bank or the ATM itself. Here\u2019s a general guide:\n\n1. **Locate an ATM**: Find an ATM that accepts cash deposits. This is usually a machine owned by your bank, but many bank-affiliated ATMs will work too.\n\n2. **Insert Your Card**: Begin by inserting your ATM or debit card into the machine and enter your PIN when prompted.\n\n3. **Select Deposit Option**: After logging in, look for the option to deposit cash. This is usually found in the main menu or under options like \u201cDeposit\u201d or \u201cTransactions\".\n\n4. **Choose Deposit Type**: You may need to select whether you are depositing cash or checks. Choose the cash deposit option.\n\n5. **Prepare Your Cash**: If the ATM has a cash deposit slot, you might need to place the cash in a specific order (for example, facing the same direction without folds or paperclips). Some ATMs will allow you to deposit bundles of cash, while others may have a limit on how many bills you can deposit at once.\n\n6. **Insert the Cash**: Insert the cash into the designated slot when prompted by the ATM. Some machines may require you to place the cash in a specific compartment.\n\n7. **Confirm Deposit Amount**: The ATM should count the bills and display the total amount on the screen. Confirm that this is correct. \n\n8. **Complete Transaction**: Follow any final prompts, which may include choosing whether to receive a printed receipt of your transaction.\n\n9. **Retrieve Your Card**: Once the transaction is completed, the ATM will return your card.\n\n10. **Take Your Receipt**: If you requested a receipt, don\u2019t forget to take it for your records.\n\nAlways follow the on-screen instructions, as they may differ depending on the ATM. If you encounter any issues or the ATM doesn\u2019t seem to be functioning properly, you may need to contact your bank for assistance.",
